Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 05-08-19.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four and one-half (4 1/2) years, eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:   
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination; 
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is entitled to 241 days sentence credit.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program and the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
Minutes.

Defendant in custody.
On counts 2 and 3, the defendant's probation was revoked effective 04-13-16.
The defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for eight (8) months, under the Huber Law, on each count, concurrent, commencing immediately.
Defendant has credit for 104 days.
The court orders a civil judgment for any unpaid financial court obligations on counts 2 and 3.
On count 1, the State has moved to vacate the Deferred Judgment Agreement.
The defendant does not contest this motion.
The Court grants the motion, vacates the Deferred Judgment Agreement and enters judgment of conviction on count 1, burglary.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two and one half (2.5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search or combination;
5) provide DNA sample;
6) pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
